#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:3
msgid "NumPy 1.6.0 Release Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:5
msgid ""
"This release includes several new features as well as numerous bug fixes and "
"improved documentation.  It is backward compatible with the 1.5.0 release, "
"and supports Python 2.4 - 2.7 and 3.1 - 3.2."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:11
msgid "Highlights"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:13
msgid "Re-introduction of datetime dtype support to deal with dates in arrays."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:15
msgid "A new 16-bit floating point type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:17
msgid "A new iterator, which improves performance of many functions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:21
msgid "New features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:24
msgid "New 16-bit floating point type"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:26
msgid ""
"This release adds support for the IEEE 754-2008 binary16 format, available "
"as the data type ``numpy.half``.  Within Python, the type behaves similarly "
"to `float` or `double`, and C extensions can add support for it with the "
"exposed half-float API."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:33
msgid "New iterator"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:35
msgid ""
"A new iterator has been added, replacing the functionality of the existing "
"iterator and multi-iterator with a single object and API. This iterator "
"works well with general memory layouts different from C or Fortran "
"contiguous, and handles both standard NumPy and customized broadcasting. The "
"buffering, automatic data type conversion, and optional output parameters, "
"offered by ufuncs but difficult to replicate elsewhere, are now exposed by "
"this iterator."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:46
msgid ""
"Legendre, Laguerre, Hermite, HermiteE polynomials in ``numpy.polynomial``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:48
msgid ""
"Extend the number of polynomials available in the polynomial package. In "
"addition, a new ``window`` attribute has been added to the classes in order "
"to specify the range the ``domain`` maps to. This is mostly useful for the "
"Laguerre, Hermite, and HermiteE polynomials whose natural domains are "
"infinite and provides a more intuitive way to get the correct mapping of "
"values without playing unnatural tricks with the domain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:57
msgid "Fortran assumed shape array and size function support in ``numpy.f2py``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:59
msgid ""
"F2py now supports wrapping Fortran 90 routines that use assumed shape "
"arrays.  Before such routines could be called from Python but the "
"corresponding Fortran routines received assumed shape arrays as zero length "
"arrays which caused unpredicted results. Thanks to Lorenz Hüdepohl for "
"pointing out the correct way to interface routines with assumed shape arrays."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:66
msgid ""
"In addition, f2py supports now automatic wrapping of Fortran routines that "
"use two argument ``size`` function in dimension specifications."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:71
msgid "Other new functions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:73
msgid ""
"``numpy.ravel_multi_index`` : Converts a multi-index tuple into an array of "
"flat indices, applying boundary modes to the indices."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:76
msgid ""
"``numpy.einsum`` : Evaluate the Einstein summation convention.  Using the "
"Einstein summation convention, many common multi-dimensional array "
"operations can be represented in a simple fashion.  This function provides a "
"way compute such summations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:81
msgid ""
"``numpy.count_nonzero`` : Counts the number of non-zero elements in an array."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:83
msgid ""
"``numpy.result_type`` and ``numpy.min_scalar_type`` : These functions expose "
"the underlying type promotion used by the ufuncs and other operations to "
"determine the types of outputs. These improve upon the ``numpy.common_type`` "
"and ``numpy.mintypecode`` which provide similar functionality but do not "
"match the ufunc implementation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:91
msgid "Changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:94
msgid "``default error handling``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:96
msgid ""
"The default error handling has been change from ``print`` to ``warn`` for "
"all except for ``underflow``, which remains as ``ignore``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:101 ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:174
msgid "``numpy.distutils``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:103
msgid ""
"Several new compilers are supported for building Numpy: the Portland Group "
"Fortran compiler on OS X, the PathScale compiler suite and the 64-bit Intel "
"C compiler on Linux."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:109
msgid "``numpy.testing``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:111
msgid ""
"The testing framework gained ``numpy.testing.assert_allclose``, which "
"provides a more convenient way to compare floating point arrays than "
"`assert_almost_equal`, `assert_approx_equal` and `assert_array_almost_equal`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:117
msgid "``C API``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:119
msgid ""
"In addition to the APIs for the new iterator and half data type, a number of "
"other additions have been made to the C API. The type promotion mechanism "
"used by ufuncs is exposed via ``PyArray_PromoteTypes``, "
"``PyArray_ResultType``, and ``PyArray_MinScalarType``. A new enumeration "
"``NPY_CASTING`` has been added which controls what types of casts are "
"permitted. This is used by the new functions ``PyArray_CanCastArrayTo`` and "
"``PyArray_CanCastTypeTo``.  A more flexible way to handle conversion of "
"arbitrary python objects into arrays is exposed by "
"``PyArray_GetArrayParamsFromObject``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:131
msgid "Deprecated features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:133
msgid ""
"The \"normed\" keyword in ``numpy.histogram`` is deprecated. Its "
"functionality will be replaced by the new \"density\" keyword."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:138
msgid "Removed features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:141
msgid "``numpy.fft``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:143
msgid ""
"The functions `refft`, `refft2`, `refftn`, `irefft`, `irefft2`, `irefftn`, "
"which were aliases for the same functions without the 'e' in the name, were "
"removed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:149
msgid "``numpy.memmap``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:151
msgid ""
"The `sync()` and `close()` methods of memmap were removed.  Use `flush()` "
"and \"del memmap\" instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:156
msgid "``numpy.lib``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:158
msgid ""
"The deprecated functions ``numpy.unique1d``, ``numpy.setmember1d``, ``numpy."
"intersect1d_nu`` and ``numpy.lib.ufunclike.log2`` were removed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:163
msgid "``numpy.ma``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:165
msgid "Several deprecated items were removed from the ``numpy.ma`` module::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:167
msgid ""
"* ``numpy.ma.MaskedArray`` \"raw_data\" method\n"
"* ``numpy.ma.MaskedArray`` constructor \"flag\" keyword\n"
"* ``numpy.ma.make_mask`` \"flag\" keyword\n"
"* ``numpy.ma.allclose`` \"fill_value\" keyword"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.6.0-notes.rst:176
msgid ""
"The ``numpy.get_numpy_include`` function was removed, use ``numpy."
"get_include`` instead."
msgstr ""
